For the performance gauge dashlet, when a value is received that is outside of the min and max value, then the gauge is drawn incorrectly. See screenshot for a correct one, versus an incorrect one. Note there is a small part that is drawn outside.

This looks like an ExtJS limitation, because using the code below at http://docs.sencha.com/extjs/4.2.2/#!/api/Ext.chart.series.Gauge also draws incorrectly:
{code}
var store = Ext.create('Ext.data.JsonStore', {
    fields: ['value'],
    data: [
        { 'value':9 }
    ]
});

Ext.create('Ext.chart.Chart', {
    renderTo: Ext.getBody(),
    store: store,
    width: 400,
    height: 250,
    animate: true,
    insetPadding: 30,
    axes: [{
        type: 'gauge',
        position: 'gauge',
        minimum: 10,
        maximum: 20,
        steps: 10,
        margin: 10
    }],
    series: [{
        type: 'gauge',
        field: 'value',
        donut: 30,
        colorSet: ['#F49D10', '#ddd']
    }]
});
{code}

(Change 9 to 14 and it draws correctly).

The fix should be that if a value is less than the min, set it to the minimum value, or if it is greater than the max, it should be set to the max value. The value drawn in the middle should be the actual value with the thresholds applied as normal.
